# Chapter 5 · Lesson 2 — build context excludes for the ingestion image.
#
# A .dockerignore keeps junk out of the build context: smaller/faster builds,
# no accidental secrets baked into a layer, reproducible images. The repo had
# none before this chapter — adding one is itself a best practice.

# Version control / project metadata
.git
.gitignore
*.md

# Python caches & build artifacts
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# Local virtualenvs — never ship the host's venv into the image
.venv/
venv/

# Local data / runtime state — must not leak into the image
chroma_data/
*.log

# Secrets — belt-and-suspenders; these must never enter the build context
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.key

# Editor / OS noise
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store

# Notebooks, tests, and course material are not needed at runtime
notebooks/
tests/
chapter_*/
clients/
pm/
